The paper formalizes the practice of strategic mining in multi-cryptocurrency markets as a game, which suggests that it belongs to the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. The paper also discusses reward design in a multi-agent system of learning agents, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with security issues in cryptocurrency markets, which could be classified under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. Finally, the paper involves the study of a multi-agent system, which could be categorized under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category.
